<title>Kittykernel - Menus</title>

<p>
Description about menus
</p>

<section>
 <title>Kittykernel</title>
 <terms>
  <item><title>Preferences</title>
   <p>Opens the <link xref="preferences">preference dialog</link>.</p>
  </item>
  <item><title>Edit blacklist</title>
   <p>Opens the <link xref="blacklist">blacklist</link> located at <code>~/.config/kittykernel/blacklist</code> in the default editor. Kittykernel needs to be restarted for any changes to take effect.</p>
  </item>
  <item><title>Quit</title>
   <p>Closes Kittykernel.</p>
  </item>
 </terms>
</section>

<section>
 <title>Kernels</title>
 <terms>
 <item><title>Refresh</title>
   <p>Refreshes the list of kernels in the repositories and PPAs without updating the cache.</p>
  </item>
  <item><title>Full refresh incl. apt</title>
   <p>Updates the apt cache and, subsequently, refreshes the list of kernels in the repositories and PPAs.</p>
  </item>
  <item><title>Refresh Ubuntu kernels</title>
   <p>Updates the list of Ubuntu mainline kernels from <code>http://kernel.ubuntu.com/~kernel-ppa/mainline/</code></p>
  </item>
  <item><title>Purge all kernels</title>
   <p>Purges all repository kernels (not the Ubuntu kernels) from the hard disk.</p>
  </item>
 </terms>
</section>

<section>
 <title>Help</title>
 <terms>
 <item><title>Help</title>
   <p>Opens the documentation you are currently reading.</p>
  </item>
  <item><title>CVE tracker</title>
   <p>Opens the Ubuntu tracker for Common Vulnerabilities and Exposures (CVE) at 
    <code>https://people.canonical.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/pkg/linux.html</code>.</p>
  </item>
  <item><title>Go to kernel.org</title>
   <p>Opens the website of the Linux kernel at <code>https://www.kernel.org/</code>.</p>
  </item>
  <item><title>Info</title>
   <p>Displays an info dialog with information on license and contributors.</p>
  </item>
 </terms>
</section>

